				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">That looks great! I love the coloring of the far background, it mixes different hues perfectly! I also love the texture and lighting on the bricks! I agree with nesrocks though, the lava river isn't immediately recognizable, and I imagine it'll be even worse if this background scrolls by and the perspective doesn't change. I think 2D games avoid this kind of pronounced perspective for a reason (unless they can distort the perspective section to make it consistent with the camera's position).<br /><br />If you really need the river to be there for whatever reason, I agree that it could use some shading to better convey the perspective, and the texture of the surface could be busier, more compressed vertically, since this is a fairly long river... you shouldn't have single &quot;bubbles&quot; covering all the distance from the middle of the river to the front most edge.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

						<table width="100%" cellspacing="0">
